# 🧠 Conventional Commit Message Template
#
# Format:
#   <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Example:
#   feat(terraform): add VM tagging support
#
# Allowed types and meanings:

# 🔨 feat – A new feature for the codebase (adds functionality)
#     Example: feat(ci): add GitHub Actions for auto-build
#
# 🐛 fix – A bug fix that corrects broken behavior
#     Example: fix(terraform): correct subnet cidr in network module
#
# 🧹 chore – Routine tasks, housekeeping, tooling changes (no user impact)
#     Example: chore(deps): bump yamllint to v1.32.0
#
# 🚀 ci – Changes to CI/CD configs or automation
#     Example: ci(github): add GCP auth to monthly workflow
#
# 📘 docs – Documentation-only changes
#     Example: docs(k8s): update deployment README with example values
#
# 💅 style – Code formatting, whitespace, semicolons, etc. (no logic change)
#     Example: style(python): apply black formatter
#
# 🔁 refactor – Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#     Example: refactor(terraform): simplify cloud-init generation logic

# Optional scopes:
#   terraform, k8s, github, docker, ceph, argo, vault, ansible, ci, monitoring, utils, deps, etc.

